ting new narratives and proposing new histories in order to show the significance of storytelling and narrative for a shared understanding of ourselves.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aMotion pictureszMexicoxHistory. 0aPsychic trauma in motion pictures. 4aFilm, Media & Cultural Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh1 aBanwell, Julia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaddu, Miriam, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aHaddu, Miriam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarris, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeen, Catherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacManus, Viviana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaza-Pérez, Maximiliano, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThornton, Niamh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWax-Edwards, Jessica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311078041340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147448055040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474480550423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474480550/original  a978-3-11-078041-3  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK